The course gives an overview of plants, algae, lichen and mushrooms, their structures, system, biology, adaptation and spread. Practical sessions introduce groups of plants, mushrooms, lichen and their most well-known representatives.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To give botanical knowledge and skills which are necessary for teaching Nature Studies as well as for practical work at the  first and second school stages and  pre-school.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  A student who has taken the subject will have  knowledge of the plant kingdom; know how to notice and solve botany-related problems in Nature Studies; have an overview of algae, lichen, mushrooms; know how to apply acquired knowledge in  teaching Nature Studies; know how to carry out practical work.
